@startuml learning-path
!theme plain

title Learning Path — Skill Progression Map

skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam activityFontSize 11

|Frontend Skills|
start
:Level 01\nWeb Vitals\n(LCP, INP, CLS);
note right
  Learn to measure
  before you optimize
end note

:Level 02\nRendering Patterns\n(SSR, CSR, Streaming);
note right
  Understand where
  time is spent
end note

:Level 03\nCaching Strategies\n(React Query, SWR, SW);
note right
  Highest-impact
  optimization
end note

:Level 04\nData Patterns\n(Infinite Scroll, Optimistic UI);
note right
  Keep UI responsive
  under data load
end note

:Level 05\nAdvanced Patterns\n(WASM, Code Splitting);
note right
  Push the boundaries
  of the browser
end note

:Level 06\nProduction Monitoring\n(Lighthouse CI, RUM);
note right
  Ship with confidence
  and visibility
end note

|Backend Skills|
:Level 01\nBenchmarking\n(autocannon, Pino);
note left
  Establish baselines
  with numbers
end note

:Level 02\nResponse Patterns\n(Streaming, JSON);
note left
  Optimize the
  wire format
end note

:Level 03\nCache Architecture\n(Redis, HTTP Headers);
note left
  Cache-aside, CDN,
  invalidation
end note

:Level 04\nDatabase Mastery\n(N+1, Indexes, Pagination);
note left
  Where most backend
  latency lives
end note

:Level 05\nConcurrency\n(Workers, Cluster, gRPC);
note left
  Scale beyond
  single-thread
end note

:Level 06\nObservability\n(OTel, Prometheus, Jaeger);
note left
  See everything
  in production
end note

:Full Stack\nProduction Ready;
note right
  Complete performance
  engineering skill set
end note

stop

@enduml
